Heat oven to 450 degrees F. Line 9-inch pie plate with crust. Carefully spread cream cheese into 6-inch circle in center. Toss apples with granulated sugar and flour; spoon over cream cheese. Fold crust partially over apples; sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Bake 25 min., covering loosely with foil the last 5 min. Cool. Serve topped with COOL WHIP. Refrigerate leftovers.